  "texts": [
    "But there are times when emotions are what create thoughts through our emotional intelligence [36].",
    "These can sometimes shape and guide our thoughts, providing us with valuable information that affects decision-making or problem-solving.",
    "For example, when we feel frustrated after a difficult task at work, this feeling can motivate us to think more creatively about how to best approach the issue in order to overcome it and deal with it better in the next phase.",
    "The interaction between these two states of mind can vary depending on the individual's personal experiences, personality traits, cultural background, etc.",
    "which ultimately shapes the way the person perceives and responds to various situations in life.In a recent scientific paper by Professor Kosinski of Stanford, it is clearly seen that Large Language Models created before 2022, such as Generative Pre-trained Transformer (GPT)-3 do not exhibit ToM as a property."
  ]
